data.text:
Awilda Lopez, the mother of a 6-year-old girl, was indicted Tuesday, Nov. 28, 1995 during a hearing at Manhattan Criminal Court. Lopez was indicted on murder charges in the death of her brutalized daughter Elisa Izquierdo, whose story touched New Yorkers and drew hundreds, many of them strangers, to her wake. (AP Photo/POOL/Susan Stava)
